[normal]1.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]ESA has played a crucial role in building a competitive and innovative space industry in Europe. ESA’s procurement principles ensure that investment by Member States helps to shape ESA programmes and they ensure that this investment is channelled back proportionately into national priority areas. 
[normal]J
[normal]uste retour
[normal] has provided a reliable 
[normal]–
[normal] and
[normal] 
[normal]accountable 
[normal]–
[normal] mechanism
[normal] 
[normal]for guaranteeing return on investment by ESA member states.
[normal] 
[normal]We
[normal] want to see these principles retained. Nevertheless, it should be noted that the UK has won a greater share of EU space research grants and infrastructure and service contracts thus far than it has invested by virtue of its membership of the EU, suggesting that the UK fares well out of both ESA’s and the EU’s procurement processes
[normal];
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
